Title: Object: A Caramanian waiwode
Series: Views in Egypt, Palestine and other parts of the Ottoman Empire
Description: Plate 12 in volume III: a waywode seated on a cushion at balcony, two other men seated by his side, three swords hung from a pillar behind, a parrot chained to the pillar and perched on a beam, three guards surrounding and watching them, one standing below steps in the foreground; after Mayer; published state. 1803 Hand-coloured aquatint with etching
Bibliographic references: Abbey Travel / Travel in Aquatint and lithography 1770-1860 from the library of J.R.Abbey (369.III.12)
